{
  "texts": [
    "This typically includes not only class constructors, all public method signatures, field declarations, and superclass or interface definitions [27,107,118] but also critical import statements [9,127] and even instructions for mocking external dependencies [108].",
    "To manage extensive context that may exceed the model's window size, researchers have proposed code reduction strategies.",
    "For instance, TestBench [167] uses AST analysis to remove irrelevant method bodies, while HITS [143] employs method slicing to decompose complex methods into manageable logical units, constructing independent contexts for each.",
    "Recent studies demonstrate that context quality significantly impacts generation performance.",
    "For example, a comprehensive evaluation by [151] indicates that including signatures of other methods in the same class (termed FCm) is the most effective feature for improving the compilation success rate of generated tests, increasing it by up to 14.92%."
  ]
}